title: Sabre GDS Business Gets New President
text:
Sabre GDS Business Gets New President September 09, 2015 
Sean Menke will join Sabre Corp. on Oct. 5 as executive vice president of Sabre and president of Sabre Travel Network, overseeing the companyâ€™s GDS business. He was executive vice president and chief operations officer of Hawaiian Airlines. Menke will replace Greg Webb, who was appointed to the new role of Sabre vice chairman, responsible for customer engagement and global development initiatives. 
-- Michele McDonald
